    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix wrong default configuration value in CU_handle_UL_RRC_MESSAGE_TRANSFER\n\n### Summary\nThe function `CU_handle_UL_RRC_MESSAGE_TRANSFER` was incorrectly treating SRB0 (ID 0) as an unexpected SRB for UL RRC messages, which contradicts 3GPP specifications. This caused issues during initial RRC connection establishment procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_cu_rrc_message_transfer.c`: Fixed SRB validation logic to properly handle SRB0 as a valid SRB according to 3GPP TS 38.331\n- Updated logging to correctly identify CCCH for SRB0 and DCCH for other SRBs\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen an initial RRC connection request is received from a UE on SRB0, the CU would incorrectly log an error message \"Unexpected UL RRC MESSAGE for SRB 0\" and potentially fail to process the connection establishment properly. This can be observed in the F1AP logs during UE attach procedures where SRB0 messages are flagged as unexpected instead of being processed normally.\n"
}